        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 5:30PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bristol, or 18 miles east of Lamar, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holly, Granada, Hartman, and Bristol.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
